    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n466" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄκρος</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ακ</span>), sup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀκρότατος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">uttermost, topmost, highest, at the
            top, end, edge</span>, or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">surface of</span> (summus);
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πόλις ἄκρη, ἄκρη πόλις</span>, ‘upper city’
            (=<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀκρόπολις</span>); <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κατ᾽ ἄκρης</span>, see <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄκρη</span>.—Adv. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄκρον</span>, ‘along
          the top,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 20.229</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
